easy = "Provide a one-sentence summary of this image, describing the main subject and the primary action or setting."
medium = "Describe this image in moderate detail. Include the main subject(s), their actions or poses, the setting or background, the dominant colors, and the overall mood or atmosphere of the scene."
hard = "Generate an exhaustive and highly detailed description of this image. Adopt the role of a forensic analyst or an art critic. Your description must cover the following aspects in depth: Overall Composition: Describe the framing, perspective (e.g., eye-level, low-angle, bird's-eye view), depth of field, and rule of thirds.Main Subjects: Provide an intricate analysis of the primary subjects, including their physical appearance, clothing (fabric texture, patterns, fit), facial expressions, body language, and any interactions between them. Lighting and Color: Specify the type of lighting (natural, artificial, harsh, soft, backlit), its direction, and its effect on shadows and highlights. Detail the color palette (dominant colors, accents, saturation, temperature). Background and Foreground: Catalog every visible element in the background, mid-ground, and foreground, no matter how small or seemingly insignificant (e.g., objects, text, signs, natural elements, imperfections). Atmosphere and Mood: Describe the sensory experience and the emotional tone conveyed by the image. Technical and Textural Details: Note textures (rough, smooth, glossy), sharpness, motion blur, or any other photographic artifacts. If text is present, transcribe it."
